'''Antonio Carvalho''' (born May 30, 1979) is a [[Canadian]] [[mixed martial artist]] currently signed to the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship|UFC]] competing in their featherweight division. He has also fought for promotions such as [[Shooto]], TKO Major League MMA, [[Maximum Fighting Championship|MFC]], Ironheart Crown, [[Cage Force]] and Warrior-1 MMA. He holds a notable victory over [[Hatsu Hioki]].

==Mixed martial arts career==

===Early career===
Carvalho made his professional MMA debut in September 2002. Over the next ten years, he fought in his native Canada and in Japan.  He amassed a record of 13 wins and 4 losses before joining the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]].

===Ultimate Fighting Championship===
In 2011, Antonio signed a multi-fight contract with the UFC and was expected to make his debut at [[UFC 134]] against newcomer [[Yuri Alcantara]]. However an injury during training forced him out of his planned UFC debut.<ref>http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Update-Pato-Carvalho-Joins-UFC-Faces-Alcantara-in-Rio-33225</ref>

Carvalho made his promotional debut against [[Felipe Arantes]] on January 14, 2012 at [[UFC 142]], losing by unanimous decision.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.winnipegfreepress.com/sports/breakingnews/canadian-featherweight-antonio-carvalho-to-make-ufc-debut-in-brazil-133978253.html|title=Canadian featherweight Antonio Carvalho to make UFC debut in Brazil|publisher=winnipegfreepress.com |date= November 16, 2011}}</ref>

Carvalho was expected to face [[George Roop]] on July 21, 2012 at [[UFC 149]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/28181/george-roop-vs-antonio-pato-carvalho-in-the-works-for-ufc-149-in-calgary.mma|title=George Roop vs. Antonio Carvalho in the works for UFC 149 in Calgary |publisher=mmajunkie.com |date=April 10, 2012}}</ref>  However, Roop was forced out of the bout with an injury and replaced by [[Daniel Pineda (fighter)|Daniel Pineda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/29397/george-roop-out-daniel-pineda-meets-antonio-carvalho-at-ufc-149.mma|title=George Roop out, Daniel Pineda meets Antonio Carvalho at UFC 149 |publisher=mmajunkie.com|date=June 26, 2012}}</ref> Carvalho defeated Pineda via KO in 71 seconds.

Carvalho next faced [[Rodrigo Damm]] on November 17, 2012 at [[UFC 154]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mmajunkie.com/news/30011/rodrigo-damm-vs-antonio-carvalho-set-for-ufc-154-in-montreal.mma|title=Rodrigo Damm vs. Antonio Carvalho set for UFC 154 in Montreal |publisher=mmajunkie.com |date=August 3, 2012 |accessdate=August 3, 2012}}</ref> He won the fight via split decision.

Carvalho then faced [[Darren Elkins]] on March 16, 2013 at [[UFC 158]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mmaweekly.com/ufc-158-fight-card-adds-antonio-carvalho-vs-darren-elkins-and-mitch-gagnon-vs-issei-tamura |title=UFC 158 Fight Card Adds Antonio Carvalho vs. Darren Elkins |publisher=MMAWeekly.com |author=Staff|date=January 21, 2013}}</ref> Carvalho lost the fight via TKO (punches) in the first round and was subsequently released from the promotion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmajunkie.com/news/2013/05/pablo-garza-and-antonio-carvalho-confirm-ufc-releases|title=Pablo Garza and Antonio Carvalho confirm UFC releases|author=MMAjunkie.com Staff|date=May 7, 2013|publisher=mmajunkie.com}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Carvalho is of [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] descent and speaks [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] fluently, having moved to [[Portugal]] from [[Canada]] at nine years old.<ref>http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:EX3r5EUVhuQJ:https://www.mmaweekly.com/carvalho-talks-pending-bout-with-hioki-2+&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=uk&client=firefox-a CARVALHO TALKS PENDING BOUT WITH HIOKI</ref>

